Hypothesis : Higher TP increases frequency and size of AllReduce → magnifies differences between algorithms.

Results: Our results are verifying the hypothesis as we are increasing the tensor parallelism we are getting the TP exposed communication time increases .Tensor Parallelism increases (TP=1→4→8), each forward and backward pass requires AllReduce operations within the TP group to synchronize activations — so both the frequency (more layers communicating) and the volume of TP communication grow. This additional TP comm burden is handled very differently by Ring vs Tree: Ring pipelines data efficiently in a bandwidth-optimal way, while Tree incurs higher latency per collective due to its tree-traversal overhead. Since these TP AllReduces are now on the critical path (growing from 0% → 47% → 61% of total comm time), the per-collective penalty of Tree gets multiplied across every layer, causing the absolute gap to widen from 62K → 109K → 142K µs as TP scales. In short, higher TP doesn't just add more communication — it repeatedly amplifies the per-collective algorithmic disadvantage of Tree over Ring.




